Senkawa High School
Baseball Club Ballpark,
Completion Commemoration Game

61
00:05:35,550 --> 00:05:39,050
Senkawa High School
Baseball Club Ballpark,
Completion Commemoration Game

62
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,900
Baseball Club

63
00:05:55,690 --> 00:05:58,560
Today, it doesn't matter
 if we win or lose.

64
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:02,500
First, play an actual game, and 
identify the areas of improvement.

65
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:09,710
The opponent made it to 
the quarterfinals last year.

66
00:06:09,710 --> 00:06:12,770
It's a suitable opponent for
 gauging where we are right now.

67
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:18,000
Let's see how good the Senkawa High School Baseball Club is.

68
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:22,320
That's what the principal said.

69
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,400
He definitely isn't an ordinary guy.

70
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,270
Right.

71
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:27,900
Let's go.

72
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:28,820
Yes, sir !

73
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,600
Ah !

74
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,210
Huh ?

75
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:39,530
I forgot.

76
00:06:47,050 --> 00:06:51,090
Dammit. They shouldn't be treating their main slugger this way.

77
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,090
Give me a break.

78
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,190
Hey, baseball club guy.

79
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,250
What ?!

80
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:23,040
Captain, they're here.

81
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,840
Yeah...

82
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:33,390
Here it is. This is the 
place you're looking for...

83
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:44,710
Man, they're far scarier than I thought...

84
00:07:44,710 --> 00:07:49,170
Father, Mother, please forgive me for dying before you...

85
00:07:50,650 --> 00:07:53,590
What are you babbling about ?

86
00:07:53,590 --> 00:07:58,610
We shouldn't judge people by
 their appearance. Right, Kunimi ?

87
00:07:58,610 --> 00:07:59,400
Yeah.

88
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:05,660
But if we meet them on the street, 
maybe we shouldn't make eye contact.

89
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:14,200
I'm Yokomichi, the
 coach for Hiryuu West.

90
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:18,900
Thank you for inviting us today.

91
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,650
I'm Koga, the coach here.

92
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:24,550
You may have heard many rumors...

93
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:29,100
...but they've learned from their 
mistakes, so please be don't worry.

94
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:31,900
Old geezer, can we start practicing ?

95
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:36,340
Can we do some pre-game practice ?

96
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:37,330
Please.

97
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:39,700
Then let us borrow
 the field for a while.

98
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:42,330
The old geezer says we can start.

99
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:02,120
It's important to properly 
maintain your equipment.

100
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,950
Both teams, line up !

101
00:09:14,050 --> 00:09:15,270
You're pitching ?

102
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:16,220


103
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,070
You're pitching ?

104
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:35,210
Yes, that's right.

105
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:42,200
If you're not confident that you can locate your pitches, don't aim for tight spots.

106
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,700
I'm a calm guy...

107
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:49,380
...but we have many short-tempered guys on our team.

108
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:53,800
Even if it just scrapes the 
uniform, you might see blood.

109
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:57,800
Sure. I'll throw everything
 right down the middle today.

110
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:02,900
Hey, hey. I'm not 
threatening you or anything.

111
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,750
Team

112
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,750
Hiryuu West

113
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,750
Senkawa

114
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,750
2

115
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,750
1

116
00:10:05,170 --> 00:10:06,570
Play ball !

117
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,190
Yeah.

118
00:10:12,190 --> 00:10:13,640
Strike ! Batter out !

119
00:10:16,740 --> 00:10:19,360
He really threw everything right down the middle.

120
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,630
I guess he's really 
underestimating us.

121
00:10:31,950 --> 00:10:33,940
Yeah ! Let's crush them !

122
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,010
We can't fool around
 against a newborn team !

123
00:10:39,010 --> 00:10:40,050
Yeah !

124
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:43,900
Go get them !

125
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:44,200
Hit them !

126
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:07,660
Out !

127
00:11:26,140 --> 00:11:27,800
Are you all right, Yanagi ?

128
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:30,200
They didn't slide into you ?

129
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:32,200
Um, no.

130
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:37,300
But really, that guy 
was going after his leg.

131
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,550
Definitely.

132
00:11:38,550 --> 00:11:40,390
That was a routine play.

133
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:47,500
It's an aggressive play to break up the double play.

134
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,270
Hit by pitch.

135
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:59,850
Any pitcher can hit
 a batter sometimes.

136
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:09,400
EYECATCH

137
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:39,560
Out !

138
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,730
Good job !

139
00:12:45,490 --> 00:12:48,000
This is awful.

140
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,500
They say that 
baseball is a combat sport.

141
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:57,440
But what if they get injured ?

142
00:12:57,440 --> 00:13:00,470
You said there are no bad people who play baseball.

143
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:03,000
That's...right, but...

144
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,690
Then you should trust your own words.

145
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,280
Out !

146
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:42,600
I had no doubt that he
 would slide into Noda.

147
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:45,900
He wanted an out, 
so he blocked the plate.

148
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:49,030
He didn't want to make
 an out, so he slid around.

149
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:50,300
That's all.

150
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:54,090
It's a routine defensive play, 
and a routine base running play.

151
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:14,090
Baseball is a combat sport...

152
00:14:14,940 --> 00:14:15,170


153
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:34,790
I'm sorry !

154
00:14:39,410 --> 00:14:40,380
Thanks...

155
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:54,600
Nice effort.

156
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:58,810
Strike !

157
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:42,000
I'm sorry. The ball got away 
from me because of the sweat.

158
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,050
I wonder about that.

159
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:45,390
Wasn't it a retaliation for 
what happened earlier ?

160
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:47,540
No, it really was the sweat.

161
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:50,180
How can we 
believe you scumbags ?

162
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:53,750
Are you saying it was intentional ?
 Don't look down on us !

163
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,660
Hit by pitch.

164
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:06,400
Don't get rattled ! It just
 scraped the uniform a little bit.

165
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,310
Watch out, Kunimi.

166
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:24,910
I don't want to say this, but they might retaliate.

167
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:26,800
Senior...

168
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,150
...your zipper's open.

169
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:30,400
...?

170
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:36,870
There's no need to worry.

171
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:41,100
There are no bad 
people who play baseball.

172
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,330
I believe that, too.

173
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:45,700
That's right.

174
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,030
Ball.

175
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:25,330
Damn. He hit my 
best pitch so easily.

176
00:17:29,050 --> 00:17:32,050
You thought he'd 
retaliate, didn't you ?

177
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,000
Huh ?

178
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,600
You've still got a ways to go.

179
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:40,550
I said there are no bad 
people who play baseball.


180
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:42,800
Oh.

181
00:17:46,770 --> 00:17:47,680
Strike !

182
00:17:48,610 --> 00:17:49,600
Yeah !

183
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,940
Can I ask you a question ?

184
00:18:02,940 --> 00:18:04,020
What is it ?

185
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:06,260
What was the "plan"
 you had just in case ?

186
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:08,400
There's no need for that now.

187
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:12,580
Yes, but just for
 reference, what was it ?

188
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:19,730
It was just a bluff.

189
00:18:25,570 --> 00:18:26,520
What ?

190
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:30,830
Did you actually play baseball 
when you were in high school ?

191
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:35,030
I was definitely in the baseball club.

192
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:40,940
I didn't get to play in a game even once in those three years, though.

193
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:47,000
The coach thoroughly hated me.

194
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:52,200
He was an absurd dictator coach.

195
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:56,080
I never understood a
 thing he was telling us.

196
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:58,650
Does that sound like sour grapes ?

197
00:18:58,650 --> 00:19:00,280
Not really.

198
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:11,480
In those three years, I kept thinking in the dugout about what I'd do if I were the coach.

199
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,300
Come to think of it...

200
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:19,070
...I probably held a desire since then to become a high school baseball coach.

201
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:23,570
Strike !

202
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,700
I'm happy that your
 dream has been realized.

203
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:32,480
Yeah.

204
00:19:40,910 --> 00:19:41,940
Wow...!

205
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:54,390
Out ! Game set !

206
00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:01,840
Did you see my super play ?!

207
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,170
Nice.

208
00:20:09,330 --> 00:20:12,670
I'm impressed that you 
squared up and hit that pitch.

209
00:20:12,670 --> 00:20:17,230
A pitch inside, and then a pitch away. That's playing it by the book.

210
00:20:17,230 --> 00:20:19,360
Sometimes, the ball 
slips away, though.

211
00:20:20,930 --> 00:20:24,340
Well, I guess I'll let
 you off the hook today.

212
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:28,400
Hiryuu West

213
00:20:29,010 --> 00:20:29,600
Huh ?

214
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:33,000
How did you like playing a
 game for the first time in a year ?

215
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,850
Don't ask me something
 that goes without saying.

216
00:20:36,850 --> 00:20:40,000
Let's go back and 
start practicing, then.

217
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,160
What ? Now ?

218
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:42,760


219
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:45,900
Hey, geezer ! What kind of 
crap are you talking about ?

220
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:51,790
We shouldn't judge people by rumors or appearances.

221
00:20:51,790 --> 00:20:52,910
I guess so.

222
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:56,220
Even then, scary people are scary.

223
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:59,270
By the way, 
who's driving that bus ?

